                      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;	<span class="subheading"> <span class="style4">&#8220;</span><span class="style2">The
                      liberal arts education</span></span><span class="bigger"> is
                      both a democratic and democratizing undertaking. The liberal
                      arts approach stresses an appreciation of knowledge, of
                      the value of critical thinking, and the improvement of
                      self rather than the value of getting a better job. Kalamazoo
                      College’s
                      Mission Statement illustrates these values, as it is written: <em>The mission of Kalamazoo College is to prepare its graduates
                      to better understand, live successfully within, and provide
                      enlightened leadership to a richly diverse and increasingly
                      complex world.</em><BR>
					  <BR>
&#8220;Kalamazoo’s approach to the liberal arts through the <em>K-Plan</em> does,
indeed, help our graduates to participate as active, informed global citizens
in a global civil society.&#8221;<br>						
